TYPES OF SHELLS:
GNOME
	Simple and modern GUI.
	Default in many distributions like Ubuntu.
	Uses menus, windows, icons, and mouse interaction.
KDE
	KDE Plasma
	Highly customizable desktop environment.
	More visual features and settings.

sh
	Bourne shell
	One of the oldest Unix shells.

Bash
	Most popular Linux shell.
	Default shell in many Linux systems.

Csh
	C shell
	Shell with syntax similar to the C programming language.

Tcsh
	
	Improved version of C shell.
	Supports command completion and editing.
	
																

Shell scripting means writing a set of commands in a file so the shell (like Bash) can execute them automatically in a Linux system. It is used to automate tasks like backups, file creation, deployments, etc.
 
